{
  "stem": "444.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They belonged to the same clubs that we did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were playing on the same team, soccer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the older brother of that family was a-- a bicyclist, on the bicycling team.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was actually no tension whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And beside that, my father was very-- a very tolerant man.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A good man.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a time when the last family moved from our house, and my brother came home, and I said, father, did you know that the Dalmans are moving out?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So my father said, that's very bad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But we still would stay because wherever the Jews are, something's happening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was the reaction of my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Something's happening meaning--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Something's happening, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] how can you say-- the Jews are more active, in-- in-- like-- like all over the world.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when sometimes anybody would be anti-Semitic in the presence of my grandmother, she always reminded them that Christ was a Jew, and that always closed the conversation.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I was brought up, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] not especially to-- to be Philo-Semite, but we just accepted the Jews like our own, and that was-- that was fine, I think.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So after the war, I-- can I start when I stopped-- when the war broke out?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When the war broke out, I was in the army.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in a battalion of-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the seashore-- defend, kind of a battalion Obrona Wybrzeza, a battalion to protect the seashore.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the war didn't-- didn't last very long, only a month in Poland, and we were captured.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I did not go to the camp because I ran away at night and changed my clothes into civilian.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was working for a short time in the same town.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
